  "prompt": "How much do partners make over a lifetime?",
  "response": "The lifetime earnings of partners can vary significantly depending on multiple factors, including their industry, geographic location, the size and success of the firm, and individual performance. For example, in the legal profession, partners at major law firms can earn substantial incomes, often reaching several hundred thousand to millions of dollars per year. Over a career spanning several decades, this can add up to several millions to tens of millions of dollars. \n\nIn the consulting industry, partners at top firms like McKinsey, BCG, or Bain can also earn substantial incomes, potentially reaching into the millions annually. Again, this would translate to significant lifetime earnings.\n\nIn finance, partners at investment banks or private equity firms can earn even higher amounts, with annual compensation often including salary, bonuses, and share of profits, leading to potentially very high lifetime earnings.\n\nIt's important to note that these are general figures and can vary widely depending on the specifics of the individual, firm, and market conditions.",
